metadata.name: Geometry tumbler #88
metadata.description:
Some arbitrary geometric shapes that hover in place until interacted with.

Each click will animate each shape to a new randomised position (x, y, z), as well as play some hits from a selection of random scales.

The longer you hold your pointer down, the more tension builds, resulting in a more intense shape displacement as well as a faster playing speed on the tones.

Doing that for long enough will also trigger one out of two effects, either putting a sepia layer over the scene or encapsulating it with a darkened vignette. There‚Äôs about a 3% chance of not getting a ‚Äúhold-in effect‚Äù but instead getting your whole scene rendered with a chromatic aberration.

There are 2 different instruments to collect. A Berlin Concert Grand Piano and a Harmonised 3-Oscillator Pad.

There‚Äôs about a 3.2% chance of getting a spheric shape instead of a cubic shape.

In addition to all this, you can get various amounts of shape counts, and each one can have a different color theming as well as different metalness and roughness materials.

There‚Äôs also a plethora of different lightings to get such as ambient, point and spotlights in different color themes.

Finally there‚Äôs a percentage indicator that reflects the uniqueness of each shape composition down to a finer detail, taking all of these parameters in account.

@computeremotions - 2022-06-19

metadata.name: Mess with Crabo #5
metadata.description:
Crabs are the heroes of legends, mysterious and dangerous creatures.

- they move around the spaces of computer games (including Minecraft, Counter-Strike, Civilization, Factorio)
- change moods (destroying Greek vineyards, wearing mask, beautiful, evaporating)
- and drawing styles (including cartoon, Takato Yamamoto)

There is a rare crab with a knife!

And a rare black mussel in a puffy Balenciaga dress

Images are generated with customised VQGAN+CLIP Python code.

metadata.name: Theatergoers #244
metadata.description:
Simple black and white blobs align to create delicate stories of an audience at their local theater. Follow their eyes in each piece to get started, but don't stare for too long‚Äî‚Äîthat's rude.

- press 's' to save the image at its current resolution
- press 'h' to say hello

20% of primary sales will be donated to https://www.cityarts.org/ and minters will receive a small royalty for all secondary sales.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #77
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: SC.002 : Studies Series #114
metadata.description:
This hybrid project combines elements of 2 previous drops: Glomularus + Inertial Packing. The project is intended as a giveaway to show appreciation to the community of collectors who previously have minted my work.

SC.002 includes multiple constraint systems, based on Verlet and Euler Integration approaches, with attached geometric primitives and softbody Prototubes. Numerous user controls are included:

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
-, +: reduce | increase Node Count
{, }: reduce | increase Packing Dimension
c, v: reduce | increase Node Adhesion
h, j: reduce | increase Node Jitter
b, n: disable| enable Node-Node Collision
z, x: reduce | increase Stick Constraint
a, s: hide | show Nodes
q, w: hide | show Wireframe
d, f: reduce | increase Prototube Thickness
p: screen capture

Tip:
1. There are 8 unique geometries, should you be inclined to collect a full set.
2. Bringing values outside of "rational" range is encouraged.

Note:
Please post your favorite SC.002 screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Traffic #20
metadata.description:
Traffic is a companion piece to Scaffold. Whilst Scaffold was intended to capture a moment in time of a single mind, Traffic aims to represent a shared moment in a community.

Outputs can be beautiful, but can also be chaotic. They can be comprised of many contributions, but a single voice may drown out many others.

All royalties go to the original minter.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution‚Ä®
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment
